Incidents of hate crime standardized by state population per 1,000,000 residents 2015-2019
1. Insert data into Tableau
2. Drag data for ‘State’ into the panel
3. Drag data for ‘2015’ into the panel under colour
4. Change the map to the world map display
5. Change the colour in the colour panel to 5 stepped shades of red
6. Change the legend to start at 0 and end with 50
7. Repeat steps 3-6 for 2016-2019

Locations of hate crimes
1. Take an average of the incidents at each location from 2015 to 2019
2. Insert filter, rearrange the averaged values in descending order, and include the averaged values larger than 100
3. Make a bar graph of the averaged incident by location
